quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,"Does he not know, when what is [buried] in the graves is turned over"
  100,10,"and what is [concealed] in the breasts is divulged"
  100,11,"on that day their Lord will be well informed about them [and their deeds]"
  101,1,The Catastrophe
  101,2,What is the Catastrophe
  101,3,What will show you what is the Catastrophe
  101,4,"[It is] the day when mankind will be like scattered moths"
  101,5,and the mountains like carded wool
  101,6,"As for him, whose deeds weigh heavy in the scales"
  101,7,he will have a pleasing life
  101,8,"But as for him, whose deeds weigh light in the scales"
  101,9,his home will be the Abyss
  101,10,And what will show you what it is
  101,11,It is a scorching fire
  102,1,"Rivalry [and vainglory] distracted you"
  102,2,"until you visited [even] the graves"
  102,3,"No indeed, soon you will know"
  102,4,"No indeed, soon you will know for yet another time"
  102,5,"Indeed, were you to know with certain knowledge"
  102,6,"you would have surely seen hell [in this very life]"
  102,7,Afterward you will surely see it with the eye of certainty
  102,8,"Then, on that day, you will surely be questioned concerning the Blessing"
  103,1,By Time
  103,2,Man is indeed in loss
  103,3,"except those who have faith and do righteous deeds, and enjoin one another to [follow] the truth, and enjoin one another to patience"
  104,1,Woe to every scandal-monger and slanderer
  104,2,who amasses wealth and counts it over
  104,3,He supposes his wealth will make him immortal
  104,4,No indeed! He will surely be cast into the Crusher
  104,5,And what will show you what is the Crusher
  104,6,"[It is] the fire of Allah, set ablaze"
  104,7,which will overspread the hearts
  104,8,Indeed it will close in upon them
  104,9,in outstretched columns
  105,1,Have you not regarded how your Lord dealt with the army of the elephants
  105,2,Did He not make their stratagems go awry
  105,3,and send against them flocks of birds
  105,4,pelting them with stones of shale
  105,5,thus making them like chewed-up straw
  106,1,"[In gratitude] for solidarity among the Quraysh"
  106,2,their solidarity during winter and summer journeys
  106,3,let them worship the Lord of this House
  106,4,"who has fed them [and saved them] from hunger, and secured them from fear"
  107,1,Did you see him who denies the Retribution
  107,2,"That is the one, who drives away the orphan"
  107,3,and does not urge the feeding of the needy
  107,4,Woe to those who pray
  107,5,but are heedless of their prayers
  107,6,—who show off
  107,7,but deny aid
  108,1,Indeed We have given you abundance
  108,2,"So pray to your Lord, and sacrifice [the sacrificial camel]"
  108,3,Indeed it is your enemy who is without posterity
  109,1,"Say, ‘O faithless ones"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,nor do you worship what I worship
  109,4,nor will I worship what you have worshipped
  109,5,nor will you worship what I worship
  109,6,"To you your religion, and to me my religion.’"
  110,1,When Allah’s help comes with victory
  110,2,and you see the people entering Allah’s religion in throngs
  110,3,"celebrate the praise of your Lord, and plead to Him for forgiveness. Indeed, He is all-clement"
  111,1,"Perish the hands of Abu Lahab, and perish he"
  111,2,"Neither his wealth availed him, nor what he had earned"
  111,3,Soon he will enter the blazing fire
  111,4,"and his wife [too], the firewood carrier"
  111,5,with a rope of palm fibre around her neck
  112,1,"Say, ‘He is Allah, the One"
  112,2,Allah is the All-embracing
  112,3,"He neither begat, nor was begotten"
  112,4,nor has He any equal.’
  113,1,"Say, ‘I seek the protection of the Lord of the daybreak"
  113,2,from the evil of what He has created
  113,3,and from the evil of the dark night when it falls
  113,4,"and from the evil of the witches, who blow on knots"
  113,5,and from the evil of the envious one when he envies.’
  114,1,"Say, ‘I seek the protection of the Lord of humans"
  114,2,Sovereign of humans
  114,3,God of humans
  114,4,from the evil of the sneaky tempter
  114,5,who puts temptations into the breasts of humans
  114,6,from among the jinn and humans.’